OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1777378266
OL,3,CFirst look: how do this year's
OL,4,Celection candidates compare?
OL,6,F52 are standing for the position of
OL,7,FDeputy; 17 are standing for the
OL,8,Fposition of Senator; and 23 are
OL,9,Fstanding for the position of Constable.
OL,11,FThis is a dramatic change from 2022's
OL,12,Felection, where 76 people stood for
OL,13,FDeputy and 16 stood for Constable (the
OL,14,Fposition of Senator was not an option).
OL,16,FIn 2018's election, 61 stood for
OL,17,FDeputy, 17 people stood for Senator,
OL,18,Fand 13 stood for Constable.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/9
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
