OL,3,CFirst look: how do this year's
OL,4,Celection candidates compare?
OL,6,F20 women and 32 men are standing for
OL,7,FDeputy; four women and 13 men are
OL,8,Fcompeting for nine seats in the
OL,9,FSenatorial race; and there are five
OL,10,Fwomen and 18 men standing to be
OL,11,FConstables across all 12 parishes.
OL,13,FIncumbents
OL,15,F41 of this year's candidates already
OL,16,Fhold positions in the current States
OL,17,FAssembly; 51 of them are incoming.
OL,19,FThis means 55.4% of this year's
OL,20,Fcandidates are hopefuls looking to be
OL,21,Fre-elected.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/9
